Template Literal Types

Template literal types (TypeScript 4.1+) allow manipulating string types at the type level, similar to JavaScript template literals.

### Basic Syntax

```typescript
type Greeting = `Hello, ${string}!`;
// Matches any string starting with "Hello, " and ending with "!"

type EventName = `on${Capitalize<string>}`;
// "on" + capitalized string
```

### Union Combinations

```typescript
type Vertical = "top" | "bottom";
type Horizontal = "left" | "right";

type Position = `${Vertical}-${Horizontal}`;
// "top-left" | "top-right" | "bottom-left" | "bottom-right"
```

### Intrinsic String Manipulation Types

| Type | Description |
|------|------------|
| `Uppercase<S>` | Converts to uppercase |
| `Lowercase<S>` | Converts to lowercase |
| `Capitalize<S>` | Capitalizes first letter |
| `Uncapitalize<S>` | Uncapitalizes first letter |

```typescript
type Upper = Uppercase<"hello">; // "HELLO"
type Lower = Lowercase<"WORLD">; // "world"
type Cap = Capitalize<"name">; // "Name"
type Uncap = Uncapitalize<"Name">; // "name"
```

### Practical CSS Pattern

```typescript
type CSSValue = string | number;

type CSSProperties = {
  [K in keyof CSSStyleDeclaration as K extends `on${string}` ? never : K]: CSSStyleDeclaration[K];
};
```

### API Endpoint Pattern

```typescript
type Resource = "users" | "posts" | "comments";
type Method = "GET" | "POST" | "PUT" | "DELETE";

type ApiEndpoint = `${Method} /api/${Resource}`;
// "GET /api/users" | "GET /api/posts" | ...
```

> **Key Point:** Template literal types generate all possible combinations of union constituents.

codeExample:
// CSS class builder
type Size = "sm" | "md" | "lg";
type Color = "primary" | "secondary" | "danger";

type ClassName = `btn-${Size}-${Color}`;
// "btn-sm-primary" | "btn-sm-secondary" | "btn-sm-danger" | ...

// Event handler type
type EventType = "click" | "focus" | "blur" | "change";
type EventHandler = `on${Capitalize<EventType>}`;
// "onClick" | "onFocus" | "onBlur" | "onChange"

// Constrained template
type HexColor = `#${string}`;

function setColor(color: HexColor): void {
  console.log(`Setting color to ${color}`);
}

setColor("#FF0000");
// setColor("red"); // Error
